prehensive; for he feared that he would somehow do something to damn himself and destroy the reputation of his family, at least bring them shame. It may have been the things his mother and aunt had told him... what an honor it was, how magnificent an oppo
rtunity; you must present yourself with total respect and grace... blah, blah, blah.\line \line \line 
